Empire Industrial Estate is one of the largest Industrial precincts in the Gold Coast Region and covers an area of over 100 ha.The 27,225 sqm site is strategically positioned at the entrance of the Estate, on the corner of Stephens Way and Peachey Road. 

This dual street frontage provides excellent exposure to the Site, which is further enhanced through its elevated position. The Site has excellent access to the wider Brisbane and Gold Coast consumer markets via the Pacific Motorway (M1), which can be accessed by either Stanmore Road (Exit 38) or Computer Road (Exit 41) on-ramps. While direct access to and from the site is provided through a dedicated left and right hand turning lane off Peachey Road, with a future signalised intersection planned to provide further ease of access.

The Site is also in proximity to major international and domestic tenants including ATCO Structures and Logistics, Cope Sensitive Freight which are located within Empire Industrial Estate as well as Caterpillar, Carlton United Breweries, OJI Fibre Solutions, Visy, Owens Illinois, Beaulieu Australia and Aldi Distribution Warehouse, which are in the surrounding area.

CBRE are pleased to present 8 Byte Street, Yatala, to the market for sale by Expressions of Interest. This property comprises a fully tenanted investment with neighbouring vacant land ready for development.

The property will be offered as follows:

Option A: Tenanted Investment Building only
- Leased to Neumann Steel 
- 3 year lease term plus option
- Medium Impact Zoning
- 3,000 sqm* Freestanding Building plus wash bay
- 8,500 sqm* land areas 
	
Option B: Undeveloped Land Only
- Subdivision and / or development opportunity
- Unimproved land area 6,110 sqm* 

Option C: Entire Site
- Future development with holding income
- Two street frontage
- This low site cover offers future expansion for existing tenants.
- Flexibility to subdivide and sell off individual lots

For inspection times and the information memorandum please contact your exclusive agents at CBRE.
